## Zero-Downtime Migrations: Expand-Contract

The most dangerous migrations are column renames and drops — they break running app instances during rolling deploys. The **Expand-Contract** pattern solves this with 3 deployment phases:

### Example: rename `user_name` → `full_name`

**Phase 1 — EXPAND** (deploy with old app still running)
```sql
-- V5__expand_add_full_name.sql
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN full_name VARCHAR(255);
UPDATE users SET full_name = user_name;  -- backfill
-- Write trigger: keep both in sync
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION sync_name() RETURNS TRIGGER AS $$
BEGIN
  NEW.full_name := NEW.user_name;
  RETURN NEW;
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql;
CREATE TRIGGER sync_user_name
  BEFORE INSERT OR UPDATE ON users
  FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION sync_name();
```

**Phase 2 — MIGRATE** (update app to use `full_name`)
```java
// Deploy new app version that reads/writes `full_name`
// Both old (user_name) and new (full_name) work during rollout
```

**Phase 3 — CONTRACT** (after all instances updated)
```sql
-- V6__contract_drop_user_name.sql
DROP TRIGGER sync_user_name ON users;
ALTER TABLE users DROP COLUMN user_name;
```
